### Is this a regression?

Sort of, new lint error introduced in the `ng update` or `ng new` in v13.

```
declare const require: {
  context(path: string, deep?: boolean, filter?: RegExp): {
    keys(): string[];
    <T>(id: string): T;
  };
};
```

should be 

```
declare const require: {
  context(path: string, deep?: boolean, filter?: RegExp): {
    <T>(id: string): T;
    keys(): string[];
  };
};
```

# 🐞 Bug report

### Command 

- [x] build
- [x] serve

### Is this a regression?

<!-- Did this behavior use to work in the previous version? -->
<!-- ✍️--> Yes, the previous version in which this bug was not present was: 11

### Description
**TLDR: How to build lazy styles files to a folder ?**

I though about postbuild process but this doesn't solve my issue with "serve".

Previous shema.json (<12) allow bundleName to have slash.
With new pattern restriction this configuration doesn't work anymore :
```
"bundleName": "assets/theme/light",
```

Shema.json from angular-cli 11:
```
"bundleName": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "The bundle name for this extra entry point."
},
```
Shema.json from angular-cli 12/13:
```
"bundleName": {
    "type": "string",
    "pattern": "^[\\w\\-.]*$", // <--
    "description": "The bundle name for this extra entry point."
},
```
## 🔬 Minimal Reproduction
Adding slash in bundleName under angular 12/13 lead to this error.
```
// build > options > styles
{
      "bundleName": "assets/theme/light",
      "inject": false,
      "input": "apps/my-app/src/assets/styles/theme/light.scss"
 },
```

## 🔥 Exception or Error

```
Property 'styles' does not match the schema.
{
  "oneOf": [
    {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "input": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "The file to include."
        },
        "bundleName": {
          "type": "string",
          "pattern": "^[\\w\\-.]*$",
          "description": "The bundle name for this extra entry point."
        },
        "inject": {
          "type": "boolean",
          "description": "If the bundle will be referenced in the HTML file.",
          "default": true
        }
      },
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "required": [
        "input"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "The file to include."
    }
  ]
}'
```

